SUMMARY:🌷🌸 ALLAN GARDENS EASTER TULIP SHOW & LUNCH 🌸🌷
DESCRIPTION:Toronto Movies & Social Group - Celebrating 14 Years!\n🌷
 🌸 ALLAN GARDENS EASTER TULIP SHOW & LUNCH 🌸🌷\n\nBlooms\, Warm Con
 servatory Air & A Classic Diner Finish\nThere’s something magical about 
 stepping into a greenhouse in early spring — especially when the city is
  still shaking off winter.\n\nJoin us for a relaxed\, social visit to Alla
 n Gardens Conservatory\, where the annual Easter flower show transforms th
 e space into a vibrant escape filled with colour\, warmth\, and the scent 
 of spring.\n\nInside the historic glass-domed Palm House (built in 1910!)\
 , you’ll find a lush collection of tropical plants alongside seasonal di
 splays bursting with tulips\, hydrangeas\, Easter lilies\, and blooming bu
 lbs.\nThis is not a formal tour.\n\nIt’s a social outing — a chance to
  wander\, take it all in\, and enjoy good company in a beautiful space.\n\
 n👉 **Don’t forget to join our WhatsApp group** – [CLICK HERE!](http
 s://chat.whatsapp.com/H59mSCbsAi018gYANrKAnc?mode=ac_t)\n\n***\n\n🚶‍
 ♂️ What We’ll Do\n\nWe’ll meet outside and head into Allan Gardens
  together\, spending about 45 minutes to an hour exploring the different g
 reenhouse rooms and seasonal Easter display.\nThere’s no rush — you’
 re free to move at your own pace\, take photos\, or just soak in the warmt
 h and colour.\nAfterward\, we’ll walk over to Fran's Restaurant\, a clas
 sic Toronto diner\, for brunch or lunch.\nYou’re welcome to join us for 
 a meal or head out after the gardens — totally up to you.\n\nSometimes t
 he best conversations happen over fries and coffee. 🍳☕\n\n***\n\n🌦
 ️ Weather & Expectations\n\nThis event will run rain or shine. The garde
 ns are indoors\, but we will be walking outside briefly between locations.
 \nPlease dress for the weather and wear comfortable shoes.\nAlso — this 
 is NOT a guided or historical tour. I’ll share bits of context casually\
 , but the focus is on social connection and enjoying the space together.\n
 \n***\n\n🧢 Meetup Details\n📍 Meetup Location: Meet me in front of Al
 lan Gradens building which is the big white building in the middle of the 
 part\n🫎 I’ll be wearing my Moose Hat\n⏰ Meetup Time: 11:00 AM\nI wi
 ll only wait 5 minutes.\nEarly is on time.\nOn time is late.\nWe’ll head
  in promptly\, so please plan accordingly and respect everyone’s time.\n
 \n***\n\n🎟️ Meetup Fee: $5 cash in person or e-transfer to\n📧 **ma
 thewmaclean@hotmail.com**\nThis helps support the group and allows us to k
 eep hosting events like this. Thank you for supporting community! 💖\n\n
 ***\n\n🎒 What to Bring\nWater\nComfortable walking shoes\nA small snack
  (optional)\nCamera or phone for photos 🌷\nWeather-appropriate clothing
 \nPlease also use the washroom before arriving\, as stops are limited.\n\n
 ***\n\n🌈 Who Is This For?\n\nThis group is open to anyone who wants to 
 be social and make friends — whether single or not.\nWe also host:\n🎬
  Movies\n🚶 Walks & hikes\n🎭 Arts & culture outings\n🍽️ Restaura
 nt gatherings\n\nThere’s always something happening.\n\n***\n\nREMEMBER:
  You’re welcome to just show up on the day if you’re unsure about your
  schedule.\nAnd as always\, sometimes plans shift and events may need to b
 e canceled — please keep an eye on updates.\n\n***\n\n👤 Organizer: Ma
 thew\nQuestions? Post on the event wall or email\n📧 torontomoviesandout
 ings@hotmail.com\n\nCome for the flowers. Stay for the warmth.\nLeave feel
 ing like you stepped into spring — even if it’s still winter outside. 
 🌸✨
